entries.title: The Papers: 'Rod attacks Tories' and 'Zahawi hands over taxes'
entries.description: Many of Friday's papers cover HMRC's investigation into Nadhim Zahawi's tax affairs and Sir Rod Stewart comments about the Tory party.

entries.title: Hunt to set out plan for growth as criticism mounts
entries.description: It will be scrutinised by businesses who claim the government has no long-term plan for the economy.

entries.title: Reanne Evans beats Stuart Bingham to become first woman to win a match at Snooker Shoot Out
entries.description: Reanne Evans beats former world champion Stuart Bingham 60-8 to become the first woman to win a match in the one-frame Snooker Shoot Out in Leicester.

entries.title: Matt Hancock paid £320K for I'm a Celebrity appearance
entries.description: The former health secretary says he donated £10,000 of the fee to two charities.

entries.title: Kolo Toure: Wigan Athletic sack boss after no wins from nine games in charge
entries.description: Wigan Athletic sack boss Kolo Toure after he failed to win any of his nine games in charge.

entries.title: Rod Stewart calls on Tories to make way for Labour
entries.description: The singer-songwriter, 78, says problems in the NHS have left the UK in the worst state he has seen.

entries.title: FA Cup predictions: Chris Sutton faces Krept from rap duo Krept & Konan
entries.description: BBC Sport football expert Chris Sutton takes on Krept from Krept & Konan to make predictions for this weekend's FA Cup ties

entries.title: Elle Edwards: Man arrested over Christmas Eve pub shooting
entries.description: The 20-year-old man has been held on suspicion of conspiracy to murder and assisting an offender.

entries.title: Leeds St James's Hospital: Man charged with planning terror attack
entries.description: A 27-year-old man is charged with planning a terror attack after the security scare at a hospital.

entries.title: Egypt archaeology: Gold-covered mummy among latest discoveries
entries.description: The mummy is found sealed inside a sarcophagus that has been unopened for 4,300 years.

entries.title: Five Memphis police officers charged over death of Tyre Nichols
entries.description: The 29-year-old was stopped in Memphis on 7 January for reckless driving and died three days later.

entries.title: Relative of Harold Shipman victim hits out at life insurance advert
entries.description: A life insurance firm said it wanted to "make people think" by using the serial killer's image.

entries.title: Sikh player in head covering row welcomes FA rule update for refs
entries.description: Charan Singh Basra, who was sent off in a row over his head covering - says the move is "needed".

entries.title: Israel-Palestinian conflict: Fears of wider flare-up after deadly Jenin raid
entries.description: What's behind the raid on the West Bank city, which led to nine Palestinian deaths on Thursday?

entries.title: Pep Guardiola: 'Mikel Arteta wouldn't celebrate goals against Arsenal'
entries.description: Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola looks back on his time working with Mikel Arteta, and recalls how his then-assistant coach would never celebrate goals against "his club" Arsenal.

entries.title: Transpennine Express boss apologises for poor services
entries.description: The head of Transpennine Express admits services have not been good enough in recent months.

entries.title: Gareth Southgate: England manager on decision to stay, World Cup & human rights
entries.description: Gareth Southgate talks to BBC sports editor Dan Roan about his decision to remain England manager, the team's performance in Qatar and why he has no regrets.

entries.title: Windrush report: Suella Braverman scraps three recommendations
entries.description: The home secretary says the changes recommended in the wake of the scandal will no longer go ahead.

entries.title: Marcelo Bielsa: Ex-Leeds boss in London for further talks with Everton over managerial vacancy
entries.description: Marcelo Bielsa arrives in London for further talks with the Everton hierarchy as they search for a successor to Frank Lampard.

entries.title: Andrew Bridgen threatens to sue Matt Hancock in Covid vaccine row
entries.description: MP Andrew Bridgen claims he was libelled, but the former health secretary is standing by his comments.

entries.title: Joanna Gosling bids an emotional farewell to BBC News live on-air
entries.description: Joanna Gosling says goodbye to viewers after 23 years in a job "that's never felt like a job".

entries.title: Ben Youngs says rugby union has 'risks' and 'rewards' following tackle height changes
entries.description: England's most-capped male player Ben Youngs insists the rewards of rugby union outweigh the risks as the debate over the controversial tackle law rages on.

entries.title: German man arrested for allegedly passing intelligence to Russia
entries.description: The suspect is believed to have been involved in a scheme to pass German intelligence to Russia.

entries.title: Artur Beterbiev v Anthony Yarde: Briton relishing underdog tag against 'scary' champion
entries.description: Anthony Yarde says he is relishing the chance to upset the odds and topple light-heavyweight champion Artur Beterbiev on Saturday.

entries.title: Vinicius Jr: Effigy prompts condemnation of 'repugnant' behaviour towards Real Madrid winger
entries.description: La Liga says it "strongly condemns acts of hatred and intimidation against Vinicius Jr" after an effigy of the Real Madrid winger is hung from a bridge.

entries.title: South Africa v England: Jofra Archer return headlines one-day series
entries.description: Jofra Archer's return headlines an otherwise low-key one-day series in South Africa that begins a crucial year for the England men's team.

entries.title: Australian Open 2023: Novak Djokovic feels he has 'something extra' at this year's tournament
entries.description: Novak Djokovic feels he has "something extra" at this year's Australian Open as he prepares to do battle for a place in the Melbourne final.

entries.title: Duncan Ferguson: Ex-Everton assistant manager named Forest Green head coach
entries.description: Forest Green Rovers appoint former Everton assistant manager Duncan Ferguson as their new head coach.

entries.title: No penalties for 'innocent' tax errors, HMRC boss says
entries.description: Tory Party chairman Nadhim Zahawi is facing calls to resign, after it emerged he paid a penalty to HMRC.

entries.title: Jacob Rees-Mogg to host GB News show
entries.description: The former business secretary will "debate the hot topics of the day", the broadcaster confirmed.

entries.title: Nitrous oxide: Ban on use and sale of laughing gas considered
entries.description: The drug, which can have damaging side effects, is thought to be a factor in anti-social behaviour.

entries.title: Transgender rapist Isla Bryson will not be imprisoned in women's jail
entries.description: First Minister Nicola Sturgeon has confirmed convicted rapist Isla Bryson will be removed from Cornton Vale.

entries.title: Olympics 2024: IOC plan for Russian & Belarusian athletes criticised by UK Government
entries.description: The IOC's plan to let Russian and Belarusian athletes compete in the 2024 Olympics is a "world away from the reality of war," says UK culture secretary Michelle Donelan.

entries.title: Michail Antonio: West Ham forward says he could leave the club in January
entries.description: West Ham forward Michail Antonio says there is a possibility he could leave the club in the January transfer window.

entries.title: Lucky escape after bus plunges into Turkey lake
entries.description: CCTV shows the driver lose control of the steering wheel in an accident that left no-one seriously hurt.

entries.title: Rachel Chinouriri joins Lewis Capaldi tour after drunk DM
entries.description: Rachel Chinouriri says being picked to support the star at his stadium shows is a dream come true.

entries.title: Katherine Brunt: England bowler retires from county cricket
entries.description: England bowler Katherine Brunt is retiring from county cricket, although she will still play in The Hundred.

entries.title: Snooker Shoot Out: Moldovan Vladislav Gradinari, 14, becomes youngest televised ranking event match winner
entries.description: Fourteen-year-old Vladislav Gradinari becomes the youngest player to win a televised ranking event match by beating Ng On Yee in the first round of the Snooker Shoot Out.

entries.title: Jail for former West Yorkshire PC who let wife take blame for speeding
entries.description: A judge says the former officer thought he could "get away with it" but had been proved wrong.

entries.title: Green claims on household basics investigated
entries.description: The competition watchdog is concerned shoppers are being "misled" about goods claiming to be green.

entries.title: Matt Hancock: Man charged with assaulting former health secretary
entries.description: The former health secretary is not thought to have been hurt in the incident on the London Underground.

entries.title: Ukraine war: Russian missiles hit Ukraine day after West's tanks move
entries.description: One person died and two others were injured after strikes in Kyiv, the city's mayor says.

entries.title: Newcastle United midfielder Joelinton fined £29k for drink-driving
entries.description: The 26-year-old midfielder was arrested while driving his Mercedes in the early hours of 12 January.

entries.title: Australian Open 2023 results: Elena Rybakina beats Victoria Azarenka to reach final
entries.description: Wimbledon champion Elena Rybakina reaches another major final as she beats two-time winner Victoria Azarenka in the Australian Open semi-finals.

entries.title: Video shows moment of cliff collapse on Dorset's Jurassic Coast
entries.description: Puffs of dust are seen in the footage before the section of cliff crumbles on to the beach below.

entries.title: Clouds gather for Rishi Sunak as cabinet meets at away day
entries.description: Two members of the prime minister's cabinet are currently under investigation over their conduct.

entries.title: Aaron Cruden & Andre Esterhuizen set to play for Barbarians against World XV
entries.description: All Black fly-half Aaron Cruden and South Africa centre Andre Esterhuizen are the latest internationals set to feature for Eddie Jones' Barbarians.

entries.title: Asteroid to pass closer than some satellites
entries.description: About the size of a bus, the space rock will whip over the southern tip of South America.

entries.title: Nine Palestinians killed in Israeli raid in Jenin
entries.description: The heaviest death toll in months comes as troops battle militants in the flashpoint West Bank town.

entries.title: Dad's warning after girl, 14, dies from inhaling deodorant
entries.description: Giorgia Green's parents want clearer product labelling to warn of the potential dangers.

entries.title: Is UK being left behind in global climate investment battle?
entries.description: The future of the planet and the global economy are entwined in a potentially risky geopolitical game.

entries.title: Ben Stokes and Nat Sciver win ICC Cricketer of the Year awards
entries.description: Ben Stokes is named ICC Men's Test Cricketer of the Year and Nat Sciver wins the women's ODI award

entries.title: Artur Beterbiev v Anthony Yarde: Arsenal to win the league & dreaming of fast food
entries.description: BBC Sport goes 12 rounds with Anthony Yarde before his world title fight against Artur Beterbiev on Saturday.

entries.title: Chester Zoo: Rare tree kangaroo emerges from mum's pouch
entries.description: The joey, the first of its kind to be born at Chester Zoo, has been developing in the pouch since July.

entries.title: Royal Mail says strikes have cost it £200m
entries.description: The owner of the mail delivery service reveals the cost of the ongoing dispute over pay and conditions.

entries.title: Novak Djokovic's father Srdjan filmed at Australian Open posing for pictures with Vladimir Putin supporters
entries.description: Novak Djokovic's father Srdjan is filmed posing for pictures with supporters of Russia president Vladimir Putin at the Australian Open.

entries.title: Leah Croucher murder suspect changed appearance - police
entries.description: Leah Croucher murder detectives believe Neil Maxwell changed his appearance to evade arrest.

entries.title: Australian Open 2023 results: Alfie Hewett into wheelchair singles and doubles finals in Melbourne
entries.description: Britain's Alfie Hewett will contest two Australian Open finals after winning his semi-finals in both the wheelchair singles and doubles.

entries.title: 'The joy of fen skating is a great metaphor for life'
entries.description: Photographer Harry George Hall captures skaters during a rare moment when conditions are just right.

entries.title: Ukraine war: Zelensky urges speedy delivery of Western tanks
entries.description: Ukraine's president says the modern fighting vehicles must be supplied quickly and in significant numbers.

entries.title: Julian Sands: New air search for actor missing in California
entries.description: A helicopter fitted with a device which can detect reflective material and even credit cards is being used.

entries.title: Court bid to protect tenants from ‘ghost landlords’
entries.description: It's hoped a ruling to define what a property landlord is will help tenants in some of England's worst homes.

entries.title: Physiotherapists, 'the quiet NHS miracle workers', walk out
entries.description: The strike across 30 services in England is the latest action by NHS staff in the pay dispute.

entries.title: Charities urge PM to stop using hotels to house migrant children
entries.description: More than 100 charities warn unaccompanied child asylum seekers housed in hotels are at risk.

entries.title: Can these rocks really power light bulbs? No, say the experts
entries.description: Viral videos of minerals with apparent electrical properties are not what they seem.

entries.title: Live music: How buying concert tickets could be made better
entries.description: Concerts can be life-affirming. Buying tickets is the opposite. Here are eight possible solutions.

entries.title: Iranian and Russian hackers targeting politicians and journalists, warn UK officials
entries.description: Politicians and journalists are being targeted with espionage attacks, the UK government is warning.

entries.title: The Papers: 'United against Putin' and 'baffling Brexit plan'
entries.description: Several of Thursday's papers lead with the West's commitment to send tanks to Ukraine.

entries.title: Subscription-based bike hire schemes on a roll
entries.description: A growing number of people are choosing to hire a bicycle over a long period of time.

entries.title: Cost of living: Cash bonuses behind record number of bank switches
entries.description: Up to £200 was offered by some banks to switching customers - prompting the most moves since 2013.

entries.title: Chuck Wepner: Honouring the real-life 'Rocky' who floored Muhammad Ali
entries.description: Chuck Wepner's most famous fight was a defeat, but his blood-soaked legend lives on in New Jersey.

entries.title: UK car production collapses to lowest for 66 years
entries.description: Car production in the UK continued to fall last year, lagging further behind the US and EU.
